<section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-12 md:px-6">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Canterbury Avenue</h1>

  <div class="prose-page mt-6">
    <p>
      Canterbury Avenue is a small site tucked away in the St Johns Road / Witchford Road
      area of the city. There are about a dozen small plots, ideal for anyone new to
      allotmenteering or uncertain about committing to a large plot on another site. The land
      was originally laid out as a children's play area serving the housing developments but
      this fell into disrepair before being converted to allotments by the City of Ely
      council.&nbsp; In common with all the town sites the soil has a clay content as this is
      on the original Isle of Ely. Mains water is installed, limited parking on adjacent
      street.
    </p>
  </div>

